criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Hospitalized stroke patients who got first-ever stroke with hemiplegia;
- Patients and/or their caregiver could understand and follow orders given by therapists;
- Patients are able to sit on the edge of beds. If not, there should be a caregiver beside during the treatment.
- Patients are isolated or quarantined due to COVID-19 or other serious infection issues.
Exclusion Criteria:
- Patients are aged over 75 years old or under 20 years old;
- The specific movement functions considered in this study are affected by any reasons of other neurological, cardiopulmonary, cancers or musculoskeletal system disease.
